parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: From ana and choreo; to retire.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: A prolonged form of an otherwise obsolete verb; to talk, i.e. Utter words.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.

parse: Personal / Reciprocal Pronoun - Accusative Masculine Plural
str2: One another, each other. Genitive plural from allos reduplicated; one another.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To do, perform, accomplish; be in any condition, i.e. I fare; I exact, require.
Worthy, worthy of, deserving, comparable, suitable. Probably from ago; deserving, comparable or suitable.
Death, physical or spiritual. From thnesko; death.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
Or desmos des-mos' neuter and masculine respectively from deo; a band, i.e. Ligament or shackle; figuratively, an impediment or disability.
